Fixes the bug in stl_validator_provided.py:
  - Normal check threshold was -0.99 (only caught perfectly inverted normals)
  - Should be < 0 (any normal pointing wrong way fails)
  - Also uses 0.0 threshold to catch any disagreement > 90 degrees
